verses.text_plain: Now gather thyself in troops, O daughter of troops: he hath laid siege against us: they shall smite the judge of Israel with a rod upon the cheek.
verses.verse_html: 1Now gather thyself in troops, O daughter of troops: he hath laid siege against us: they shall smite the judge of Israel with a rod upon the cheek.

verses.text_plain: But thou, Beth–lehem Ephratah, though thou be little among the thousands of Judah, yet out of thee shall he come forth unto me that is to be ruler in Israel; whose goings forth have been from of old, from everlasting.
verses.verse_html:
2But thou, Beth–lehem Ephratah, though thou be little among the thousands of Judah, yet out of thee shall he come forth unto me that is to be ruler in Israel; whose goings forth have been from of old, from everlasting. ▼
▼ everlasting: Heb. the days of eternity

tokens.text: out of thee shall he come forth

footnotes.body_text: ▼ everlasting: Heb. the days of eternity
footnotes.body_html: ▼ everlasting: Heb. the days of eternity

verses.text_plain: Therefore will he give them up, until the time that she which travaileth hath brought forth: then the remnant of his brethren shall return unto the children of Israel.
verses.verse_html: 3Therefore will he give them up, until the time that she which travaileth hath brought forth: then the remnant of his brethren shall return unto the children of Israel.

tokens.text: Therefore will he give them up

verses.text_plain: And he shall stand and feed in the strength of the Lord, in the majesty of the name of the Lord his God; and they shall abide: for now shall he be great unto the ends of the earth.
verses.verse_html:
4And he shall stand and feed in the strength of the Lord, in the majesty of the name of the Lord his God; and they shall abide: for now shall he be great unto the ends of the earth. ▼
▼ feed: or, rule

tokens.text: for now shall he be great

verses.text_plain: And this man shall be the peace, when the Assyrian shall come into our land: and when he shall tread in our palaces, then shall we raise against him seven shepherds, and eight principal men.
verses.verse_html:
5And this man shall be the peace, when the Assyrian shall come into our land: and when he shall tread in our palaces, then shall we raise against him seven shepherds, and eight principal men. ▼
▼ principal: Heb. princes of

footnotes.body_html: ▼ principal: Heb. princes of

verses.text_plain: And they shall waste the land of Assyria with the sword, and the land of Nimrod in the entrances thereof: thus shall he deliver us from the Assyrian, when he cometh into our land, and when he treadeth within our borders.
verses.verse_html:
6And they shall waste the land of Assyria with the sword, and the land of Nimrod in the entrances thereof: thus shall he deliver us from the Assyrian, when he cometh into our land, and when he treadeth within our borders. ▼
▼ waste: Heb. eat up
 , ▼
▼ in the…: or, with her own naked swords

verses.text_plain: And the remnant of Jacob shall be in the midst of many people as a dew from the Lord, as the showers upon the grass, that tarrieth not for man, nor waiteth for the sons of men.
verses.verse_html: 7And the remnant of Jacob shall be in the midst of many people as a dew from the Lord, as the showers upon the grass, that tarrieth not for man, nor waiteth for the sons of men.

verses.text_plain: And the remnant of Jacob shall be among the Gentiles in the midst of many people as a lion among the beasts of the forest, as a young lion among the flocks of sheep: who, if he go through, both treadeth down, and teareth in pieces, and none can deliver.
verses.verse_html:
8And the remnant of Jacob shall be among the Gentiles in the midst of many people as a lion among the beasts of the forest, as a young lion among the flocks of sheep: who, if he go through, both treadeth down, and teareth in pieces, and none can deliver. ▼
▼ sheep: or, goats

verses.text_plain: Thine hand shall be lifted up upon thine adversaries, and all thine enemies shall be cut off.
verses.verse_html: 9Thine hand shall be lifted up upon thine adversaries, and all thine enemies shall be cut off.

verses.text_plain: And it shall come to pass in that day, saith the Lord, that I will cut off thy horses out of the midst of thee, and I will destroy thy chariots:
verses.verse_html: 10And it shall come to pass in that day, saith the Lord, that I will cut off thy horses out of the midst of thee, and I will destroy thy chariots:

tokens.text: And it shall come to pass in that day
of thee, and I will destroy

verses.text_plain: And I will cut off the cities of thy land, and throw down all thy strong holds:
verses.verse_html: 11And I will cut off the cities of thy land, and throw down all thy strong holds:

verses.text_plain: And I will cut off witchcrafts out of thine hand; and thou shalt have no more soothsayers:
verses.verse_html: 12And I will cut off witchcrafts out of thine hand; and thou shalt have no more soothsayers:

verses.text_plain: Thy graven images also will I cut off, and thy standing images out of the midst of thee; and thou shalt no more worship the work of thine hands.
verses.verse_html:
13Thy graven images also will I cut off, and thy standing images out of the midst of thee; and thou shalt no more worship the work of thine hands. ▼
▼ standing…: or, statues

tokens.text: of thee; and thou shalt no more worship

verses.text_plain: And I will pluck up thy groves out of the midst of thee: so will I destroy thy cities.
verses.verse_html:
14And I will pluck up thy groves out of the midst of thee: so will I destroy thy cities. ▼
▼ cities: or, enemies

tokens.text: of thee: so will I destroy

verses.text_plain: And I will execute vengeance in anger and fury upon the heathen, such as they have not heard.
verses.verse_html: 15And I will execute vengeance in anger and fury upon the heathen, such as they have not heard.
